Here, kitty, kitty, kitty, kitty.

31
00:01:50,143 --> 00:01:55,080
That's weird.
Cats can't open drawers, can they?

32
00:01:55,148 --> 00:01:58,049
- You didn't leave them open?
- No way.

33
00:01:59,652 --> 00:02:02,587
Wow. Do you think somebody broke in?

34
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:10,022
[Both] Mr. Whiskers?

35
00:02:19,839 --> 00:02:22,103
[Susan] Mr. Whiskers?

36
00:02:22,175 --> 00:02:24,609
Though she didn't know it at the time,

37
00:02:24,677 --> 00:02:30,316
Susan's luck...
had finally started to change.

38
00:03:11,824 --> 00:03:15,282
News that an intruder had breached
the security of Wisteria Lane

39
00:03:15,395 --> 00:03:17,590
spread like wildfire.

40
00:03:17,697 --> 00:03:20,257
At a Neighborhood Watch meting
the next night,

41
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:22,494
residents voiced their concerns

44
00:03:30,243 --> 00:03:32,609
whenever she took a shower.

45
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:35,977
Bob Fisk warned those present
that a government agency

46
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:38,677
was listening in
on their phone conversations.

47
00:03:38,751 --> 00:03:42,517
Helen Vale spoke of
a ruthless local tenage gang

48
00:03:42,589 --> 00:03:44,648
that had egged her minivan.

49
00:03:45,959 --> 00:03:48,018
Three factors contribute to...

50
